				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cerene" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(872489); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=872489&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205698" alt="Cerene" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=872489)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cerene" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(872489); return false;" >Cerene</a></span> <span class="odate time_1446016696 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Oct 2015 07:18</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2398263">
									

<p>I think I cracked it!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;For&nbsp;those&nbsp;who&nbsp;come&nbsp;after:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;We&nbsp;came&nbsp;before:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The clue is in the final communication. &quot;The week where you had me with the third item in the list, the breach alarm, was much better — I'd definitely say I was an A those times.&quot; The third item. The third letter in Draber is A. So you assign numbers to the items (Launcher is 1, Anchor is 2, Alarm is 3, Suit is 4), then take the <em>n</em>th number of the name of each person, where <em>n</em> is the number of the item they're assigned. Except the Class Ds, because they've been &quot;made Es&quot;, so they're all, of course, E. So, starting with Morris and going around the circle clockwise, you get REMEMBER.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

